<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulunaltoadsnatcher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 1:51:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19147.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~bookfolk/_uimages/music4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Graffe.com Official Class Title Poll</span><hr size=1> I didn't like any of the choices above.  Arcanist is nice sounding, but too general, which I think is the problem also with sage.<br>
<br>
I think of our best trait as channeling through our spells and, of course, doing beaucoup damage.  Good at focusing in the midst of chaos and doing great deal of damage.  Perhaps a name that evokes great mental prowess.  Mensa comes to mind although it is regrettably colloquial.  Savant is along the lines but has the stigma of &quot;idiot savant.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Maybe Sapient.  <br>
<br>
Too bad they took my favorite title, Erudite, and ruined it by tieing it to a bunch of non-green Leader look-alikes.  GRRRR.<br>
 <p><font face="Cornerstone"><font size=-1>Lunal Toadsnatcher</font></font><BR><font face="Cornerstone"><font size=-1><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163741">Gnome Wizard of the Noble Drake (49)</a></font></font><BR><font face="Palacio"><font size=-1>Tholuxe Paells</font></font><BR><font size=-2><font face="Intrepid">Leader of </font><i><font face="Diploma"><a href="http://pub63.ezboard.com/btheelectoftholuxepaells">The Elect</a></font></i></font><BR><font face="Tahoma"><font size=-1>"<i>Nuke em from point blank range.  Its the only way to be sure</i>."</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaberen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aberen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 2:00:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19147.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Graffe.com Official Class Title Poll</span><hr size=1> I actually LIKE the idea of Seer.  If wizards are the protectors and seekers of arcane (read: obscure) knowledge, then Seer fits us best.  Besides, we do get ports, sight line spells, and are 'supposed' to be wise.  In my experience, wizards (just the players) tend to be great record-keepers (uhm, isn't Graffe's the BEST class specific site? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and people with all sorts of random knowledge.<br>
<br>
Besides, Seer sounds good with just about any name, and creates an alliteration with Sorcerer.<br>
<br>
Seer Name Name the Sorcerer.<br>
<br>
Vote Seer. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137660"> Aberen Kindheart </A>            Sorcerer  and Council Member of Alliance of the Arcane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=starlighten>Starlighten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 2:10:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19147.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://starlight.mw.mw/~eq/signatures/starlighten-sq.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Graffe.com Official Class Title Poll</span><hr size=1> Seer sounds more like a shamanic title to me... more wis-like.<br>
<br>
Savant and Solist might sound good but I'm not quite sure they feel right.<br>
<br>
Wobbling between voting for Arcanist or Other, but I can think of no title offhand that I would like better... Sorcerer would be nice but I don't quite like the &quot;double&quot; effect...<br>
<br>
I'm going to think about this for a while before voting I think. Just posting some thoughts. <p><hr>
