<br><b>Silvershadow</b> - Shadow Knight of 39 fearkites <i>Mithril Force</i>
<br><b>Starzinger</b> - Bard of 11 hit songs <i>Kena</i>
<br><i>Solusek Ro server</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucazanplanewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cazan Planewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 2:25:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19147.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/carlsond1/MiniCazan.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Graffe.com Official Class Title Poll</span><hr size=1> I find that there just isn't an adequate term to describe the role of the wizard in EQ.  <br>
<br>
Wizard and sorceror (and magician for that matter) all conjure up ideas of one who is skilled in magic in general.  I really want something more specific, and, well, special.  <br>
<br>
Arcanist isn't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> even a word</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> so I can't really go much for that.  Plus the root of it, Arcane, doesn't really even go to the heart of what a wizard is in EQ.  Arcane means difficult to explain or understand, mysterious.  EQ Wizards are far from that.  We nuke things.  We port places.  That's it.  Pretty straightforward.  <br>
<br>
Sapient is a fancier (and more arcane ccc) way of saying Sage.  And being erudite and wise is all fine but the term doesn't exactly roll off the tongue, is too obscure, and really isn't the connotation I want in the term in front of my name. <br>
<br>
What I want is a term that makes people think of a magic version of a Terminator.  One that makes you think of massive nukes, major destruction.  Sadly, nothing really does that.  So lacking that Sorceror is the most apt term.  Or if we are making up terms, Arch Wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulunaltoadsnatcher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 2:35:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19147.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~bookfolk/_uimages/music4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Graffe.com Official Class Title Poll</span><hr size=1> Arch Wizard I like.  Of course if you want to use a made up term we could call ourselves &quot;Uber&quot; or &quot;Ubermensch.&quot;  No tongue roll there.<br>
<br>
Maybe when we reach the right level of AA, lvl 60, FT80, our entire names should all be eliminated and replaced simply with &quot;Rombus.&quot;   <p><font face="Cornerstone"><font size=-1>Lunal Toadsnatcher</font></font><BR><font face="Cornerstone"><font size=-1><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163741">Gnome Wizard of the Noble Drake (49)</a></font></font><BR><font face="Palacio"><font size=-1>Tholuxe Paells</font></font><BR><font size=-2><font face="Intrepid">Leader of </font><i><font face="Diploma"><a href="http://pub63.ezboard.com/btheelectoftholuxepaells">The Elect</a></font></i></font><BR><font face="Tahoma"><font size=-1>"<i>Nuke em from point blank range.  Its the only way to be sure</i>."</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Moderator</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Verant's #1 Fanboy</font></td></tr></table><br><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><font color=#FFFFFF>Contact Rombus</font></a></font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 3:00:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19147.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Graffe.com Official Class Title Poll</span><hr size=1> Arcanist is based off of Arcane.  You can see it in use in zones such as Ssra Temple (the proud snake Wizards that pullers fear use it!).  A majority of the people in-game seem to know what an Arcanist is and associate it with Wizards.  Personally I feel it's the most fitting.<br>
<br>
Savant... well, it's ok.  I'd say it fits a bit better on an Enchanter and even then it's still kind of general.  Yes, we're scholars, but every casting class is really made up of scholars. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Solist is someone's name (already been said).<br>
<br>
Seer is more of a priest-class title.  I don't know, we're not really prophets hehe.<br>
<br>
Sorcerer is a good title and it would be my choice as well... if it wasn't already our level 60 title.  I think that when you chose a title you want something that's unique and fits you well.  Sorcerer may be unique, but it's too redundant.  Also, Sorcerer Soandso the Sorcerer will look stupid. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway!  Voting on Arcanist~ <p><br>
